# Platform-suffixed sidecar binaries are large (Temporal ~500 MB,
# Deno ~100 MB on macOS) and not source. They are either:
#   - downloaded by `console/scripts/fetch-temporal-binaries.sh`
#     and `console/scripts/fetch-deno-binaries.sh`
#   - or fetched per-platform inside the desktop-release.yml CI workflow
#
# Local dev: copy your system binary into the matching slot, e.g.
#   cp "$(which temporal)" temporal-aarch64-apple-darwin
#   cp "$(which deno)"     deno-aarch64-apple-darwin
#
# Track README.md and any scripts; ignore the binaries themselves.
temporal-*-apple-darwin
temporal-*-unknown-linux-gnu
temporal-*-pc-windows-msvc
temporal-*-pc-windows-msvc.exe
deno-*-apple-darwin
deno-*-unknown-linux-gnu
deno-*-pc-windows-msvc
deno-*-pc-windows-msvc.exe
!*.md
!*.sh
